<TR BACKGROUND="" BGCOLOR="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=3><TABLE WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD WIDTH=200 ALIGN="LEFT">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/cgi-bin/advent.pl?day=1&show_all=1"><font size=2>&lt;&lt;&lt;&nbsp;DEC&nbsp;1</font></a></TD><TD WIDTH=200 ALIGN="CENTER"><a href="/cgi-bin/advent.pl"><font size=2>HOME</font></a></TD><TD ALIGN="CENTER"><a class="addthis_button" href="http://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php?v=250&amp;pub=xa-4b157e7f1b908808"><img src="http://s7.addthis.com/static/btn/v2/lg-share-en.gif" width="125" height="16" alt="Bookmark and Share" style="border:0"/></a><script type="text/javascript" src="http://s7.addthis.com/js/250/addthis_widget.js#pub=xa-4b157e7f1b908808"></script></TD><TD WIDTH=200 ALIGN="RIGHT"><a href="/cgi-bin/advent.pl?day=3&show_all=1"><font size=2>DEC&nbsp;3&nbsp;&gt;&gt;&gt;</font></a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR>
<TR HEIGHT=5><TD COLSPAN=3 BACKGROUND="" BGCOLOR="#000000"></TD></TR>
<TR><TD WIDTH=5 BACKGROUND="" BGCOLOR="#000000"></TD>
<TD BACKGROUND="/black6.png">
<TABLE CELLPADDING=5><TR><TD>
	<TABLE WIDTH=100% CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR><TD>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=130 HEIGHT=130 SRC="chocs/choc_day_2.png" ALT="chocolate"><IMG ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=190 SRC="globes/advent_globe_2.png" ALT="snowglobe"><table cellpadding=10 align="center" background="/black4.png" width=430><TR><TD><center><font size=6 color="#ffff00"><b><i>R-TYPE</i></b></font><br><font size=3 color="red"><b><i>23 days to Christmas</i></b></font></center></TD></TR></TABLE><p>
Another game from the bumper crop of Christmas 1988, and the story
starts in the summer when, out of the blue, large colourful
screenshots were sprinkled throughout the preview pages of the
magazines.
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<TABLE ALIGN="right" WIDTH=300 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD><a href="pngs/d2_1988_ad10.png" target="1988_ad10.png"><IMG SRC="pngs/d2_1988_ad10_small.jpg" WIDTH=300 HEIGHT=207></a></TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSPAN=1 ALIGN="CENTER"><font size=-1 color="yellow"><b><i>A very bold double-page advert that seeing it on-screen rather than on-paper doesn't do justice to it.</i></b></font></TD></TR>
</TABLE>1988 had marked the return of colour to coin-op conversions, with
<i>Karnov</i> and <i>Bionic Commando</i> leading the way. But whilst the unfair
gameplay of <i>Karnov</i> held it back, and <i>Bionic Commando</i> only used colour
in the backgrounds, the programmers of the <i>R-Type</i> conversion were
going for large, detailed, clear, fast colourful graphics filling the screen - a rarity
on the Speccy. The screenshots looked gorgeous on the printed page,
and even back in that Summer I started hoping that the finished game
would be as good as it looked.
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<TABLE CELLPADDING=10 ALIGN="left"><TR><TD><TABLE WIDTH=222 ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="MIDDLE" BGCOLOR="#000000" BACKGROUND=""><TR><TD><center><object width="212" height="172"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/mLtShuLqyz0&hl=en_GB&fs=1&"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/mLtShuLqyz0&hl=en_GB&fs=1&" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="212" height="172"></embed></object><br>
<FONT size=-1 COLOR="#FFFF00"><b><u>Coca Cola Adverts Remix</u></b></font></center><font size=-1 color="#ffffff">Beautiful - I couldn't miss this out. Someone's made a remix of the Christmas Coke Trucks adverts and it looks very fab indeed. Unmissable. <b><i>(1:34)</i></b></font><center><font size=-2 color="#ffffff"><i>Watch full-sized <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mLtShuLqyz0" target="mLtShuLqyz0">at YouTube</a></font></center></TD></TR></TABLE><br></TD></TR></TABLE>
As far as hype went, <i>R-Type</i> had very little of it. No long-running
hype-building ad campaign. No freebies that I can remember, like
badges, booklets, stickers, that sort of thing. This was one title
which hyped itself purely by itself - the screenshots alone could only
make the reader drool with anticipation. The preview features almost
wrote themselves - half a dozen screenshots would match a few
paragraphs of puff quite easily.
<TABLE ALIGN="center" WIDTH=300 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD><a href="pngs/d2_1988_pre4.png" target="1988_pre4.png"><IMG SRC="pngs/d2_1988_pre4_small.jpg" WIDTH=300 HEIGHT=211></a></TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSPAN=1 ALIGN="CENTER"><font size=-1 color="yellow"><b><i>Look at those huge colourful graphics - this feature showed that it wasn't just magic and sorcery, and it really was the Speccy doing it all.</i></b></font></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE CELLPADDING=10 ALIGN="left"><TR><TD><TABLE WIDTH=222 ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="MIDDLE" BGCOLOR="#000000" BACKGROUND=""><TR><TD><center><object width="212" height="172"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/J11NIQJdO5Q&hl=en_GB&fs=1&"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/J11NIQJdO5Q&hl=en_GB&fs=1&" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="212" height="172"></embed></object><br>
<FONT size=-1 COLOR="#FFFF00"><b><u>Scrooged Trailer</u></b></font></center><font size=-1 color="#ffffff">One of my favourite Christmas movies - probably a little <i>too</i> sweet at the end, but a very watchable romp. <b><i>(2:37)</i></b></font><center><font size=-2 color="#ffffff"><i>Watch full-sized <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J11NIQJdO5Q" target="RK_xRPs2QqI">at YouTube</a></font></center></TD></TR></TABLE><br></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE CELLPADDING=10 ALIGN="right"><TR><TD><TABLE WIDTH=222 ALIGN="CENTER" VALIGN="MIDDLE" BGCOLOR="#000000" BACKGROUND=""><TR><TD><center><object width="212" height="172"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/bmj7KlIut1w&hl=en_GB&fs=1&"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/bmj7KlIut1w&hl=en_GB&fs=1&" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="212" height="172"></embed></object><br>
<FONT size=-1 COLOR="#FFFF00"><b><u>Original Band Aid Broadcast</u></b></font></center><font size=-1 color="#ffffff">You never see the full length version on the music channels, so here's a little bit of history. <b><i>(5:21)</i></b></font><center><font size=-2 color="#ffffff"><i>Watch full-sized <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bmj7KlIut1w" target="xhpKe45mSFg">at YouTube</a></font></center></TD></TR></TABLE><br></TD></TR></TABLE>
C+VG magazine took the unusual step of releasing a demo of the first
level on the cover of their magazine - rare for a multiformat
publication. Then BAM! Right in front of your eyes you saw these
incredible graphics whizzing about, accompanied by some rather
appropriate 48k sound effects.
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;But <i>R-Type</i> wasn't a victory of style of substance - this shoot-em-up
had several aces stuck up its sleeve. The dockable pod added strategy
to the blasting - do you use it as a shield or as a remote blaster? -
and the nasties were so varied that they raised the standard for
future shoot-em-ups. One level was travelling around the outside of a
giant spaceship taking out its defences one by one - I had never seen
anything like that before. Neither had I seen end-of-level "bosses"
before, especially on this scale where they'd fill up half the screen -
and of course they were as colourful and well animated as they were
deadly.
<TABLE ALIGN="center" WIDTH=300 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD><a href="pngs/d2_1988_rev3.png" target="1988_rev3.png"><IMG SRC="pngs/d2_1988_rev3_small.jpg" WIDTH=300 HEIGHT=220></a></TD></TR>
<TR><TD COLSPAN=1 ALIGN="CENTER"><font size=-1 color="yellow"><b><i>There could only be one outcome...</i></b></font></TD></TR>
</TABLE>That demo had sold the game to me - the reviews were a mere formality
as I'd already ordered the game by the time they were published. I
never got too far into it - level four is an absolute bitch if you're
not a hardcore gamer - but it still took me a while to finish those
first three levels.
<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE><p>
</TD></TR></TABLE>
</TD><TD WIDTH=5 BACKGROUND="" BGCOLOR="#000000"></TD></TR>
